{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[G3 child-coverage audit — parent safe-luge-nog/b4d4-3369-6dd2-41e6, this child as one of two consumers]\n\n4-bucket map of parent criteria vs children (roster: 908c link-consumer + ba2c parent-consumer):\n- SC1 (primitive consumed by BOTH parent+link, no Jira logic in gate): FULLY (joint) — 908c consumes gate for links, ba2c for parent.\n- AC1 (reducer maintains/folds managed_refs, never reduced by UNLINK): STRUCTURAL — primitive-build is parent's own in-scope work; consumers only read it.\n- AC2 (survives compact_ticket; compact-then-reconcile test): COVERED behaviorally — 908c AC5 'survives a compaction boundary' + ba2c 'across a compaction boundary'; restore mechanism is parent-side.\n- AC3 (SNAPSHOT byte-parity / deterministic serialization): STRUCTURAL — parent-owned serialization.\n- AC4 (shared should_propagate_removal consumed by BOTH outbound paths): FULLY (joint) — 908c link path + ba2c parent path.\n- AC5 (reclamation prunes converged refs + test): STRUCTURAL — parent Scope explicitly lists 'reclamation' as primitive's own deliverable, not a consumer.\n- AC6 (docs/ template for future providers): STRUCTURAL — parent Scope explicitly lists 'docs establishing the reusable pattern'.\n\nResult: no uncovered parent criterion attributable to children. Parent is a primitive-building story that carves reducer/byte-parity/reclamation/docs into its OWN in-scope work and tracks only the two CONSUMERS as children; both consumer halves are covered (links here, parent in ba2c). Clean for G3."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782536811777342001,"uuid":"9f227072-342c-4851-b772-380e0e3db139"}